 external; blatant or subtle, common or sublime, far or near — are clingable,
 offer sustenance, and are accompanied with mental fermentation: those are
 called fabrication as a clinging-aggregate.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Whatever consciousness — past, future, or present; internal or external;
 blatant or subtle, common or sublime, far or near — is clingable, offers
