 or subtle; common or sublime; far or near: that is called the aggregate
 of form.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Whatever feeling is past, future, or present; internal or external; blatant
 or subtle; common or sublime; far or near: that is called the aggregate
 of feeling.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Whatever perception is past, future, or present; internal or external;
 blatant or subtle; common or sublime; far or near: that is called the aggregate
 of perception.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Whatever (mental) fabrications are past, future, or present; internal or
 external; blatant or subtle; common or sublime; far or near: those are
 called the aggregate of fabrication.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Whatever consciousness is past, future, or present; internal or external;
 blatant or subtle; common or sublime; far or near: that is called the aggregate
 of consciousness.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"These are called the five aggregates.
\end_layout

