\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A giver of what is a giver of strength? A giver of what, a giver of beauty?
 A giver of what, a giver of ease? A giver of what, a giver of vision? And
 who is a giver of everything? Being asked, please explain this to me.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
[The Buddha:]
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A giver of food is a giver of strength.
 A giver of clothes, a giver of beauty.
 A giver of a vehicle, a giver of ease.
 A giver of a lamp, a giver of vision.
 And the one who gives a residence is the one's who's a giver of everything.
 But the one who teaches the Dhamma is a giver of the Deathless.
\end_layout

