 at Jeta's Grove, Anathapindika's monastery.
 Now at that time a large number of monks, after the meal, on returning
 from their alms round, had gathered at the meeting hall and were engaged
 in many kinds of bestial topics of conversation: conversation about kings,
 robbers, & ministers of state; armies, alarms, & battles; food & drink;
 clothing, furniture, garlands, & scents; relatives; vehicles; villages,
 towns, cities, the countryside; women & heroes; the gossip of the street
 & the well; tales of the dead; tales of diversity, the creation of the
 world & of the sea; talk of whether things exist or not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then the Blessed One, emerging from his seclusion in the late afternoon,
 went to the meeting hall and, on arrival, sat down on a seat made ready.
