\begin_layout Standard
§ 3.2.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
[Sister Vimala:]
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Intoxicated with my complexion figure, beauty, & fame; haughty with youth,
 I despised other women.
 Adorning this body embellished to delude foolish men, I stood at the door
 to the brothel: a hunter with snare laid out.
 I showed off my ornaments, and revealed many a private part.
 I worked my manifold magic, laughing out loud at the crowd.
 Today, wrapped in a double cloak, my head shaven, having wandered for alms,
 I sit at the foot of a tree and attain the state of no-thought.
 All ties — human & divine — have been cut.
 Having cast off all effluents, cooled am I, unbound.
