\begin_layout Standard
The coming-together of these factors is called the stream because it leads
 inevitably to two things, just as the current of a tributary will lead
 inevitably to a major river and then to the sea.
 In the immediate present, the stream leads directly to the arising of the
 Dhamma eye, the vision that actually constitutes this first awakening.
 Over time, the stream ensures that — in no more than seven lifetimes —
 one will be totally Unbound.
\end_layout

